title: Any Command: Control Your PC from Android Phone | Any Command
text: Featured by HowToMen In their Top 15 Android Apps of JuneControl your PC with ease — your way.Turn your phone into a customizable remote with unlimited shortcut possibilities. From launching apps to automating key combos, create the perfect setup for your workflow.Also includes built-in mouse and keyboard support so you can navigate and type from anywhere.Simple. Fast. Fully yours.Media & StreamingSpotify / iTunes / VLC – control playback, volume, skip tracksYouTube (via browser) – skip ads, pause, fullscreen toggle (especially handy with your Chrome extension)Netflix / Disney+ / Prime Video – simple controls while watching on a second screenAbleton Live / FL Studio / Cubase – trigger clips, control transport, quick access to effectsPremiere Pro / DaVinci Resolve / After Effects – timeline navigation, tool switching, render/exportPhotoshop / Lightroom – brush size, undo/redo, tool switchingCreative & Audio ProductionGaming & EmulationProductivity & OfficeEmulators (e.g., Cemu, PCSX2, Dolphin) – map gamepad-style shortcutsOBS Studio / Streamlabs – start/stop stream, scene switching, mute micMinecraft / Flight Sims / MMOs – trigger complex macros or in-game functions with easeMicrosoft Excel / Word / PowerPoint – navigation, formatting shortcuts, macrosNotion / Obsidian / OneNote – open specific pages, toggle checklistsRemote Desktop / Virtual Machines – full control while away from keyboardFantastic app to control your PC. There are many possible uses, as you can customize the shortcuts to any keyboard key combination.Wonderful to use. Great ui. Quick connection★★★★★★★★★★
